title: Coffea arabica
Chemical Constituents: Caffeine, tannin, fixed oil, carbohydrates, and proteins
Therapeutic uses: Act as analgesic, anaphrodisiac, anorexic, antidotal, cardiotonic, CNS-stimulant, counterirritant, diuretic, hypnotic, and folk remedy for asthma, atropine-poisoning, fever, flu, headache, jaundice, malaria, migraine, narcosis.
